    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But \"careful judicial review\" sounds like a way to just delay the inevitable. If a law is meant to protect everyone—like, say, healthcare access or civil rights—how can you justify letting a religious group opt-out of it? Doesn't that effectively allow them to impose their specific moral code on the rest of society by creating these loopholes? It feels like you're prioritizing religious tradition over the actual progress of civil rights and equality.",
